entity.name: Justice Department says seized Mar-a-Lago materials list is ‘full and accurate’
entity.description: The Justice Department submitted a revised inventory of the materials seized in the August 8 search of former president Donald Trump’s residence at Mar-a-Lago — with an affidavit indicating that the new inventory list fully reflects what was taken, despite unfounded claims of planted evidence, according to CNN. During the search, FBI agents removed thousands of government documents and objects mixed with classified materials as part of the Justice Department’s investigation into his handling of government materials.

entity.name: Queen Elizabeth II is laid to rest at Windsor Castle
entity.description: The monarch’s funeral was attended by an estimated 2,000 guests, including world leaders and heads of state, according to the BBC. After the state funeral, the coffin was taken to Windsor Castle, England for a committal service, followed by a private family ceremony. The Queen, who died on September 8 at the age of 96, was buried alongside her late husband Prince Philip and her parents, King George VI and the Queen Mother.
